  "text": "Reconstructing lineage trees using FastTree. When inferring complete cell lineage trees in the simulations of SOLiD sequencing data (N =65,536 cells), we used an heuristic method that approximates the Maximum Likelihood approach, implemented by the FastTree software [CITATION_1] . FastTree was chosen for its ability to infer trees from large alignments, consisting of tens of thousands of sequences, and for doing so very efficiently.",
